                    <span>Gloman's new book, "303 Digital Filmmaking Solutions", is a practical book that new digital filmmakers and veterans alike will find useful in using to solve filmmaking problems. The digital age is here and this book covers the gamut from preproduction to post production.<BR>One of the best things Gloman did was to arrange the subjects in relatively short segments for quick reading on each solution. <P>Pulling from over twenty three years of experience, the author relates so many practical and low cost ways to make digial filmmaking a success for you. These little tibits and real life learning experiences that Gloman shares will save you time and money in your own productions.<P>You can skip reading this book and take years to learn the skills covered in "303 Digital Filmmaking Solutions", or read the book and shortcut your way to success. <P>This book is highly recommended.</span>
                  
              
